!ccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccc
! TJ: Input file for periodic channel flow
!ccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccc

! Grid size  !T (Should be the same as (ngx,ngy,ngz) in "param.inc"
33	nix
33	niy
9	niz

! Domain size
1.			xL	domain length
52.1		yL	domain height
1.			zL  domain width

! Mesh parameters
0	imeshY	stretching in Y: (0)uniform (1)pw-linear (2)matched tanh (3) Gauss-Lobatto
40.	ratio

! Initial field parameters
1	ifield		(1)zero (2)uniform (3)parabolic (4)dummy
0	iturb		add random fluctuations?
0	iOSS		read orr-sommerfeld/squire data? (0)no (1)yes
0	iPeriodic	add periodic perturbations?      (0)no (1)yes
1.	ubulk
0.	wbulk

! Boundary conditions
0	BC_bottom (0)no-slip (1)free-slip
0	BC_top	  (0)no-slip (1)free-slip

! Orr-Sommerfeld / Squire perturbation parameters (iOSS.ne.0)
3       nmodes		number of modes

1.12	alp_oss		streamwise wave# of 1st mode
0.0		beta_oss	spanwise   wave# of 1st mode
0.03	eps_oss		amplitude of 1st mode

1.12	alp_oss2	streamwise wave# of 2nd mode
2.1		beta_oss2       spanwise   wave# of 2nd mode
0.001	eps_oss2        amplitude of 2nd mode

1.12	alp_oss3	streamwise wave# of 2nd mode
-2.1	beta_oss3       spanwise   wave# of 2nd mode
0.001	eps_oss3        amplitude of 2nd mode

! Periodic perturbation parameters	(iPeriodic.ne.0)
0	alp	streamwise wavenumber integer
2	beta	spanwise   wavenumber integer
0.000	eps_x	streamwise perturbation epsilon
0.001	eps_z	spanwise   perturbation epsilon

! Flow parameters
100.		Re			Reynolds number
180.		Re_tau		Friction Reynolds number
0.0001574	epsilon		Perturbation epsilon (Set to 1.0 if you've already scaled your perturbations!)

! Textured surface BCs
2	bot_txtr (0) no-slip (1) free-slip (2) stream-wise micro-ridges (3) micro-posts
0	top_txtr (0) no-slip (1) free-slip (2) stream-wise micro-ridges (3) micro-posts
8	ikz_txtr    Integer wavenumber in z-direction
1	ikx_txtr    Integer wavenumber in x-direction
32	zspn_txtr   Feature width in z-direction
4	xspn_txtr   Feature width in x-direction
0.09375	Az_txtr     Amplitude of feature oscillation in z-direction (normalized by channel half-height)
